                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="79528" author="adilger" created="Mon, 17 Mar 2014 18:01:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to clarify - there are separate options &quot;flock&quot;, &quot;localflock&quot;, and &quot;noflock&quot; that enable/disable the flock behaviour for the mountpoint.  This is different from the &quot;nolock&quot; feature being tested here, which disables DLM locking entirely and forces the application to handle the file consistency on its own.  I believe that this would work if you are doing O_DIRECT page-aligned and page-sized IO.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to Jinshan, this is just a problem in setting the file size correctly, so maybe it will be a small fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note also that this feature has very rarely been tested, so it will take some work to get into shape.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
